B 8.00 structural leaf N gN kgC-1

V 1.20 photosynthesis parameter kgC m-2 yr-1
k 0.50 saturate rate of carbon gain w/LAI unitless
G 1.33 Growth of carbon cost unitless
s 500.00 soil decomposition residence time yr kgC m-2
a_r 0.50 allocation to roots unitless
u 0.50 N uptake ability constant yr gN-1
N_tot 100.00 total N in system gN
parameter value description unit
sigma 0.02 leaf mass per area kg C m-2
lambda 0.57 leaf lifespan yr kgC-1 m2
n 1.66 leaf N content per area gN m-2
R 0.02 leaf respiration per area kgC m-2 yr-1
tau 10.00 decomposition time yr

Equilibria

## <environment: R_GlobalEnv>
state EQ.value description units
NL 5 N in leaves gN m-2
N_lit 88 N in litter gN m-2
NS 7 N in soil gN m-2

Timeseries Simulations

Model is written on a per m2 ground area basis, tracking nitrogen in leaves, litter, and soil. State variables are gN / m2 ground.

Initial Conditions

state value description units
N_tot 100 total ecosystem N gN m-2
NL.0 50 initial stock of N in leaves gN m-2
NS.0 50 initial stock of N in soil gN m-2

N-limited Integration

t = seq(from=0,to=50,by=1/365) # t in years, integration on a daily timestep (0.00274)
out = ode(y=y.0,times=t,func=grow_plant_n_limited,parms=p_derived) %>% as_tibble() 
colnames(out) <- c("time", "NL", "NS")

# derived states and rates
output <- out %>% 
  ## calculate litter
  mutate(N_lit = p_derived$N_tot - NL - NS) %>% 
  # calculate leaf area
  mutate(L = NL/n) %>% 
  ## calculate c flux rates 
  mutate(photo = (n/sigma)*(V/k)*(1-exp(-k*L)),
         resp = (n/sigma)*(R + G*sigma/lambda)*L,
         net_gain = photo-resp) %>% 
  ## calculate instantaneous N fluxes
  mutate(n_uptake = u*a_r*NS*NL,
         n_litterfall = NL/lambda,
         n_min = N_lit/tau)

## derived states and rates
output <- out %>% 
  ## calculate litter
  mutate(N_lit = p_derived$N_tot - NL - NS) %>% 
  # calculate leaf area
  mutate(L = NL/n) %>% 
  ## calculate c flux rates 
  mutate(photo = (V/k)*(1-exp(-k*L)),
         resp = (R + G*sigma/lambda)*L,
         net_gain = photo-resp) %>% 
  ## calculate N-limitation
  mutate(c_lim_uptake = (n/sigma)*net_gain) %>% 
  ## calculate instantaneous N fluxes
  mutate(n_lim_uptake = u*a_r*NS*NL,
         n_litterfall = NL/lambda,
         n_min = N_lit/tau)

Note this seems unreasonable because there is no check on NOT depleting nitogen below the amount in the soil with C-limitation only!

Fluxes

This is reflected in the negative N-uptake rate under nitrogen limitation (not operating in this system).
